reviewText: I AM DEAF AND I LOVE BETH MOORE BUT WAS SO DISAPPOINTED THAT THE DVD WAS NOT CLOSED-CAPTIONED.
You just can't go wrong with Beth Moore.  This was a gift for my sister and she loved it!
Oh this precious woman's love for God and other women come out so beautifully on this video. This is such an encouragement both to the new in faith and the mature in the faith.
I have not been able to get the CD to work.  Each of the CD players I have tried it in tells me there is nothing to play.  Just haven't returned it yet.

Extraordinary Women-A Woman's Prayer Life.  I really enjoyed this DVD and would recommend it to others.
Beth Moore is an excellent speaker.

Absolutely love this dvd!  I gave my copy to my mother-in-law, so I'm having to buy another copy for myself.  Another reviewer says Beth Moore sits in her chair the whole time.  True.  Says it's boring.  Not true.  It's a very calming, prayerful dvd.  I've watched it several times - when I need a bit of prayerful calm in my life.  It's powerful.

I watched this DVD with a small group of ladies- we found it boring and perhaps dated.  Of course the message is great, if you can stay awake to watch/hear it.  Beth Moore sits in her chair the entire hour.  This DVD lacks energy!!!
Beth Moore is well worth listening to. This DVD has been such an encouragement! Can't go wrong with this - well worth your time.
